139
00:06:20,374 --> 00:06:21,428
Xiao Lin.

140
00:06:22,772 --> 00:06:24,132
It's your birthday tomorrow.

141
00:06:24,991 --> 00:06:26,530
How about getting you a cake?

142
00:06:28,312 --> 00:06:29,460
I don't think so.

143
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:31,694
It's boring when it's only
you and me celebrating it.

144
00:06:41,601 --> 00:06:43,038
The dishes are not done.

145
00:06:43,062 --> 00:06:44,366
All the alcohol you drink.

146
00:06:47,507 --> 00:06:48,655
The floor is not mopped.

147
00:06:48,679 --> 00:06:50,858
The house is such a mess
when Mom is not home.

148
00:07:21,444 --> 00:07:23,413
(Ouyang Fugui: Hello, why are you silent?)

149
00:07:26,475 --> 00:07:28,959
(Don't send me a message.)

150
00:07:28,992 --> 00:07:31,342
(I'm just curious and only looking around.)

151
00:07:31,366 --> 00:07:33,951
(I'm straight.)

152
00:07:36,336 --> 00:07:39,101
(Ouyang Fugui sent you a message)

153
00:07:40,983 --> 00:07:42,271
You are straight?

154
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:43,537
I don't buy it.

155
00:07:43,561 --> 00:07:45,561
I'm running out of inspiration for my writing.

156
00:07:45,585 --> 00:07:48,351
It especially makes me want to
talk and get some fresh air.

157
00:08:03,694 --> 00:08:05,248
I'm currently drafting a novel.

158
00:08:17,771 --> 00:08:20,709
How about you come out and
we can see how it goes?

159
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:23,451
Let's take a walk
when there is nothing else to do.

160
00:08:23,881 --> 00:08:25,225
It doesn't hurt to make friends, right?

161
00:08:54,014 --> 00:08:54,896
You’re done eating?

162
00:08:55,373 --> 00:08:56,194
Yes.

163
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,780
What are you going to do?

164
00:09:00,077 --> 00:09:01,154
Just going out.

165
00:09:02,951 --> 00:09:04,436
Where? It's late.

166
00:09:09,146 --> 00:09:10,694
Come back early in the evening.

167
00:09:10,718 --> 00:09:11,818
Your grandmother is coming.

168
00:09:12,397 --> 00:09:13,381
Got it.

169
00:09:40,616 --> 00:09:41,264
Hey.

170
00:09:41,881 --> 00:09:42,850
Hello.

171
00:09:43,178 --> 00:09:44,022
Sorry.

172
00:09:44,046 --> 00:09:44,732
Thank you for waiting.

173
00:09:44,756 --> 00:09:46,060
Oh, no, I just arrived too.

174
00:09:46,928 --> 00:09:47,741
Let's go.

175
00:09:48,256 --> 00:09:49,068
Yeah.

176
00:09:55,850 --> 00:09:57,334
Why are you keeping such a distance from me?

177
00:09:57,358 --> 00:09:58,600
Don't worry. I'm not going to eat you.

178
00:09:58,913 --> 00:10:00,061
It’s all right.

179
00:10:01,326 --> 00:10:03,568
So, it's your first time meeting someone?

180
00:10:03,593 --> 00:10:04,560
Oh, yes.

181
00:10:05,795 --> 00:10:07,357
What kind of novel are you working on?

182
00:10:08,264 --> 00:10:11,006
It's actually in the area of news.

183
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:13,209
I often tend to write novels in my spare time.

184
00:10:13,584 --> 00:10:14,522
I recently just

185
00:10:14,546 --> 00:10:15,607
published a book as well.

186
00:10:15,889 --> 00:10:17,115
That's great.

187
00:10:17,693 --> 00:10:18,678
I guess.

188
00:10:18,702 --> 00:10:20,568
Actually, I also like writing.

189
00:10:20,593 --> 00:10:21,819
and reading is a preferred activity for me.

190
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:23,865
What do you read then?

191
00:10:23,889 --> 00:10:24,982
All of it.

192
00:10:25,006 --> 00:10:28,240
Locally, Wangbo's Drifting
Beijing Shanghai and Guangzhou.

193
00:10:28,264 --> 00:10:30,732
Internationally, The Great Gatsby.

194
00:10:31,045 --> 00:10:31,983
That's great.

195
00:10:32,592 --> 00:10:34,061
You sure read a lot.

196
00:10:34,085 --> 00:10:35,154
What's your major?

197
00:10:35,178 --> 00:10:36,670
I'm in the Chinese Department.

198
00:10:37,475 --> 00:10:38,842
Let's take a walk inside.

199
00:10:39,655 --> 00:10:40,662
Cool.

200
00:10:42,389 --> 00:10:46,037
Personally, I perfer Duna Barnes.

201
00:10:46,061 --> 00:10:47,131
Who is Duna Barnes?

202
00:10:47,155 --> 00:10:49,123
A female writer from the States.

203
00:10:49,147 --> 00:10:51,303
She is actually homosexual.

204
00:10:51,764 --> 00:10:53,818
But she refuses to admit it.

205
00:10:53,843 --> 00:10:54,857
Just like you.

206
00:10:55,131 --> 00:10:56,506
What do you mean like me?

207
00:10:56,538 --> 00:10:58,693
Then, why did you say you are straight?

208
00:10:59,568 --> 00:11:01,021
I am.

209
00:11:01,779 --> 00:11:02,975
Or

210
00:11:02,999 --> 00:11:04,170
I may say I'm bisexual.

211
00:11:04,194 --> 00:11:05,732
I've had a couple of girlfriends.

212
00:11:06,991 --> 00:11:08,342
Oh, impressive.

213
00:11:08,889 --> 00:11:11,037
Then why did you download the app?

214
00:11:11,561 --> 00:11:13,725
I'm just being curious.

215
00:11:14,123 --> 00:11:15,342
The same reason I met you.

216
00:11:15,982 --> 00:11:17,256
After all,

217
00:11:17,881 --> 00:11:19,623
I've never met any gays in my real life.

218
00:11:20,491 --> 00:11:21,967
It's not that you haven't seen them.

219
00:11:21,991 --> 00:11:23,967
There must be some around you,

220
00:11:24,584 --> 00:11:26,217
but you just don't know about them.

221
00:11:27,155 --> 00:11:28,068
Really?

222
00:11:28,092 --> 00:11:28,990
Maybe.

223
00:11:29,014 --> 00:11:30,951
Your name is Ouyang Fugui?

224
00:11:33,194 --> 00:11:34,631
A lot of people call me that.

225
00:11:34,913 --> 00:11:35,810
However,

226
00:11:35,834 --> 00:11:37,310
I made that name up.

227
00:11:37,702 --> 00:11:38,866
For me,

228
00:11:38,890 --> 00:11:40,420
an earthy first name

229
00:11:40,444 --> 00:11:43,482
sounds funny especially when it comes
after a rather nobel last name.

230
00:11:44,131 --> 00:11:44,983
Which grade are you in?

231
00:11:45,007 --> 00:11:45,920
I'm a freshman.

232
00:11:46,577 --> 00:11:48,038
Have you ever been to the woods?

233
00:11:48,062 --> 00:11:49,670
Is there an area that is accessible?

234
00:11:49,694 --> 00:11:50,490
Yes.

235
00:11:50,514 --> 00:11:51,021
Let's go.

236
00:11:51,045 --> 00:11:51,935
I'll show you around.

237
00:12:02,608 --> 00:12:04,202
Wow, what a nice place.

238
00:12:04,226 --> 00:12:05,771
I can't believe I've never been here before.

239
00:12:06,077 --> 00:12:08,381
Didn't you ever try to step out?

240
00:12:08,405 --> 00:12:09,326
Never.

241
00:12:09,350 --> 00:12:10,795
I thought there weren't any more routes around here.

242
00:12:11,357 --> 00:12:12,951
Every cloud

243
00:12:12,975 --> 00:12:14,373
has a silver lining.

244
00:12:14,818 --> 00:12:15,491
Go.

245
00:12:15,515 --> 00:12:16,326
Let's go to the river.

246
00:12:16,350 --> 00:12:17,350
How can I get there?

247
00:12:17,374 --> 00:12:18,779
Cross it over.

248
00:12:22,373 --> 00:12:23,702
For a town as small as ours,

249
00:12:23,726 --> 00:12:26,482
this is the only place
where you can see the bridge clearly.

250
00:12:34,741 --> 00:12:36,037
By the way,

251
00:12:36,061 --> 00:12:37,678
are you going to get married?

252
00:12:37,702 --> 00:12:38,615
Marry?

253
00:12:39,194 --> 00:12:40,030
No way.

254
00:12:40,054 --> 00:12:41,451
Why should I get married?

255
00:12:41,717 --> 00:12:43,279
Would it be a disaster for the girl
if I was to marry her?

256
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:46,740
Your family knows you're gay?

257
00:12:46,764 --> 00:12:48,529
Yes, I came out.

258
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:50,038
Awesome.

259
00:12:50,592 --> 00:12:51,920
What was their reaction like?

260
00:12:52,224 --> 00:12:53,248
In the beginning,

261
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:54,928
they surely disagreed.

262
00:12:55,264 --> 00:12:56,975
They forced me to go on a blind date or something.

263
00:12:57,623 --> 00:12:59,084
Bit after a while,

264
00:12:59,109 --> 00:13:00,537
when they realized that I was good on my own,

265
00:13:00,866 --> 00:13:02,006
then they quit.

266
00:13:02,357 --> 00:13:03,725
Thereafter,

267
00:13:03,749 --> 00:13:05,248
it's my mom who comforted my dad.

268
00:13:06,186 --> 00:13:09,068
I'm friendlier with my mother.

269
00:13:09,795 --> 00:13:11,131
She accepted it more quickly.

270
00:13:13,139 --> 00:13:14,475
I guess

271
00:13:14,508 --> 00:13:18,506
most gays have a better relationship
with their mother than with their father.

272
00:13:19,318 --> 00:13:20,435
You too, right?

273
00:13:24,115 --> 00:13:26,295
My parents got divorced.

274
00:13:28,163 --> 00:13:29,287
Oh.

275
00:13:29,311 --> 00:13:30,506
I'm sorry to hear that.

276
00:13:30,530 --> 00:13:31,756
No worries.

277
00:13:34,694 --> 00:13:37,920
So your parents are cool with you living
with your boyfriend, right?

278
00:13:39,834 --> 00:13:41,365
Well, we've broken up for a while now.

279
00:13:41,991 --> 00:13:42,912
